                     <interp inst="t17641212-81-person623" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to the prosecutor: the two prisoners came into the shop as I was shutting it up, on the 28th of October, about twelve at night; Mallet took up a loin of mutton, and said, Weigh this: I put it in the scale: in the mean time Simpson took a hat from off-the hook, and went round me, and as he was going out at the door, I stopped him with it in his hand: Mallet got out at the door, and took it out of Simpson's hand, and away he ran, and I after him: a watchman stopped him, and another pursued Simpson, and took him: the hat was found by a watchman, flung behind the shop.</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. I was sent for, and when Mallet was taken, he behaved very impudently, and threatened to destroy me if ever he got his liberty.</p>
               <p>The prisoners, in their defence, said they went in to buy some meat, but denied the fact laid to their charge.</p>
